Adelaide Crows captain Taylor ` Tex ' Walker was pictured offering a helping hand to a seven-year-old girl who burst into tears just moments before leading the AFL side onto the field .
Satine Cahill was serving as the team 's mascot ahead of North Melbourne at Adelaide Oval on Sunday .
But the pig-tailed youngster became spooked by the fireworks and rumbling 47,000 fans in the stadium .
The touching moment between the 24-year Melbourne goal scorer and the blonde schoolgirl was captured by photographers .